        "title": "fix(agents): suggest recovery for unknown tool ids",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Fixes #92273 by making Tool Search unknown-id failures actionable instead of returning only a bare `Unknown tool id` message.\n- Adds closest-match suggestions for guessed tool ids such as `file_write` when the catalog contains `write`.\n- Points the recovery turn to the canonical Tool Search path: `tool_search`, `tool_describe`, then `tool_call` with the exact id or name.\n\n## Behavior or issue addressed\n\n#92273 describes Tool Search `mode: \"tools\"` breaking pre-compaction memory flush recovery when the model guesses a tool id such as `file_write`. The prior error only said `Unknown tool id: file_write`, leaving the silent recovery turn without enough information to select the managed `write` tool. This patch preserves the original error prefix but adds close matches and explicit recovery steps.\n\n## Real environment tested\n\nLocal OpenClaw repository worktree on branch `fix/issue-92273-tool-search-recovery`, using the repository-pinned package manager via `corepack pnpm@11.2.2`.\n\n## Exact steps or command run after this patch\n\n```bash\ncorepack pnpm@11.2.2 --dir /media/vdb/migrated-from-root-media-vdc/code/ai/aispace/openclaw-worktrees/issues-83437-92273 exec vitest run src/agents/tool-search.test.ts -t \"suggests recoverable Tool Search steps for guessed tool ids|preserves code-mode bridge errors from the child process\"\n```\n\n```bash\ngit -C /media/vdb/migrated-from-root-media-vdc/code/ai/aispace/openclaw-worktrees/issues-83437-92273 diff --check\n```\n\n## Evidence after fix\n\n```text\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\n     Tests  4 passed | 86 skipped (90)\n  Duration  9.89s\n```\n\n```text\ngit diff --check\n# no output\n```\n\n## Observed result after fix\n\nA guessed `file_write` tool id now fails with a recoverable diagnostic that includes `Did you mean: write?` and directs the model to use `tool_search`, `tool_describe`, and `tool_call` with the exact id or name. The target `write` tool is not executed on the failed guessed-id call.\n\n## What was not tested\n\nA full live pre-compaction memory flush run was not executed. The proof is a focused local Tool Search runtime regression covering the unknown-id recovery diagnostic and the existing code-mode bridge error path.\n\n## Risk\n\nLow. The change is scoped to Tool Search unknown-id error formatting. Existing callers that match the `Unknown tool id: ...` prefix continue to see that prefix, while recovery turns receive additional actionable guidance.",
